items.sentence: You never seem to pay much attention in class.
You never seem to be interested in helping us.
You never seem to be interested in doing that.
You never look like you're having a good time.
You have to change trains at the next station.
You should apologize to Tom for what you said.
You didn't really mean what you said, did you?
You didn't tell Tom where to meet us, did you?
You have to tell me exactly what I need to do.
You were the one who told me it was safe here.
